    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The Utilities sector, amongst many other sectors, has made a decent recovery and has a lot of room to the upside.</p>

<h3 id="20170131-xlu">XLU</h3>


<p><a href="/images/blog/20170131/xlu.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170131/xlu.png" alt="XLU - 2017-01-31 - Daily" /></a>
XLU - Steady trend up</p>

<p>Overall, the trend here is clearly up, making it a great sector to go long some stocks.</p>

<p>Here are some of the best stocks to buy, offering great risk/reward in the upcoming short term in the utilities sector:</p>

<h3 id="20170131-lnt">LNT</h3>


<p><a href="/images/blog/20170131/lnt.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170131/lnt.png" alt="LNT - 2017-01-31 - Daily" /></a>
Great recapture and successful retest of the 200MA. Today confirmed, offering great trade location.</p>

<h3 id="20170131-ppl">PPL</h3>


<p><a href="/images/blog/20170131/ppl2.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170131/ppl2.png" alt="PPL - 2017-01-31 - Daily" /></a>
As discussed in another <a href="/blog/2017/01/31/why-the-bears-got-trapped/" title="PPL Long">recent post</a>. This one closed above 200MA, and continued strength in the sector can get this stock up to previous highs.</p>

<h3 id="20170131-es">ES</h3>


<p><a href="/images/blog/20170131/es2.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170131/es2.png" alt="ES - 2017-01-31 - Daily" /></a>
Very similar to LNT, with lots of room to the upside.</p>

<h3 id="20170131-xel">XEL</h3>


<p><a href="/images/blog/20170131/xel.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170131/xel.png" alt="XEL - 2017-01-31 - Daily" /></a>
Very similar to all of the above, also with lots of room to the upside.</p>

